name: Yanma
flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

name: Yanmega
flavorText: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Celebi
flavorText: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal an Energy card you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Cacnea
flavorText: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

name: Tropius
flavorText: Bunches of delicious fruit grow around its neck. In warm areas, many ranches raise Tropius.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your discard pile to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Rowlet
flavorText: At a distance, it launches its sharp feathers while flying about. If the enemy gets too close, Rowlet switches tactics and delivers vicious kicks.
Ability1Text: If you played Bird Keeper from your hand during this turn, ignore all Energy in this Pokemon's attack costs.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dartrix
flavorText: It throws one knifelike feather after another at its enemies, and each one precisely strikes a weak point. These feathers are known as blade quills.

name: Decidueye
flavorText: As if wielding a bow, it launches the arrow quills hidden among the feathers of its wings. Decidueye's shots never miss.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon V and Pokemon-GX.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dhelmise V
Attack1Text: If any of your Grass Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Giga Hammer.

name: Dhelmise VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon for each Grass Energy attached to this Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Max Anchor.

name: Grookey
flavorText: When it uses its special stick to strike up a beat, the sound waves produced carry revitalizing energy to the plants and flowers in the area.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Thwackey
flavorText: The faster a Thwackey can beat out a rhythm with its two sticks, the more respect it wins from its peers.
Ability1Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this Pokemon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Rillaboom
flavorText: By drumming, it taps into the power of its special tree stump. The roots of the stump follow its direction in battle.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gossifleur
flavorText: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokemon.

name: Eldegoss
flavorText: The cotton on the head of this Pokemon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarnâ€”a Galar regional specialty.
Attack1Text: Heal all damage from 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Zarude
flavorText: Once the vines on Zarude's body tear off, they become nutrients in the soil. This helps the plants of the forest grow.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Reshiram
flavorText: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 60 damage to itself.

name: Cinderace V
Ability1Text: If a Stadium is in play, this Pokemon has no Retreat Cost.

name: Cinderace VMAX
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does that much more damage.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Horsea
flavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

name: Kyogre
flavorText: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.
Attack1Text: This attack does 80 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Buizel
flavorText: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

name: Floatzel
flavorText: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

name: Manaphy
flavorText: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokemon.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 6 cards of your deck, reveal a Pokemon you find there, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Volcanion
flavorText: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 120 damage for each heads.

name: Chewtle
flavorText: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokemon bites down and never lets go.

name: Drednaw
flavorText: This Pokemon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Cramorant
flavorText: This hungry Pokemon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokemon other than its preferred prey.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Snom
flavorText: It spits out thread imbued with a frigid sort of energy and uses it to tie its body to branches, disguising itself as an icicle while it sleeps.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Frosmoth
flavorText: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Water Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Water Pokemon.

name: Shinx
flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has 3 or fewer Prize cards remaining, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Luxio
flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if you drew this Pokemon from your deck at the beginning of your turn and your Bench isn't full, before you put it into your hand, you may put it onto your Bench.

name: Luxray
flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon evolved from Luxio during this turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Rotom
flavorText: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Item cards that have the word "Rotom" in their name, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokemon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: As it eats the seeds stored up in its pocket-like pouches, this Pokemon is not just satisfying its constant hunger. It's also generating electricity.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Morpeko V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Morpeko VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Indeedee V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Trapinch
flavorText: Its nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in, there is no escape.
Attack1Text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Its body is full of poisonous gas. It floats into garbage dumps, seeking out the fumes of raw, rotting trash.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Galarian Weezing
flavorText: This Pokemon consumes particles that contaminate the air. Instead of leaving droppings, it expels clean air.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is in the Active Spot, your opponent's Pokemon in play have no Abilities, except for Neutralizing Gas.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. Put 4 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokemon during Pokemon Checkup.

name: Spinarak
flavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

name: Crobat V
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand. You can't use more than 1 Dark Asset Ability each turn.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Crobat VMAX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is Knocked Out.

name: Nickit
flavorText: Aided by the soft pads on its feet, it silently raids the food stores of other Pokemon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.
Attack1Text: Your opponent shuffles their hand and puts it on the bottom of their deck. If they put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, they draw 3 cards.

name: Thievul
flavorText: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent, it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Cufant
flavorText: It digs up the ground with its trunk. It's also very strong, being able to carry loads of over five tons without any problem at all.

name: Ditto V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may choose a Basic Pokemon V from your discard pile and switch it with this Pokemon. Any attached cards, damage counters, Special Conditions, turns in play, and any other effects remain on the new Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.

name: Ditto VMAX
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from Eevee, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Greedent V
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Cramorant V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Cramorant VMAX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Indeedee
flavorText: It uses the horns on its head to sense the emotions of others. Males will act as valets for those they serve, looking after their every need.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Alcremie V
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Alcremie VMAX
Attack1Text: For each of your Benched Pokemon, search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to that Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard any amount of Energy from your Pokemon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
